 events. In the case of NS-NS mergers, however,\nneutrino emission of the accreting and viscously spreading torus is too short\nand too weak to yield enough energy for the outflows to break out from the\nsurrounding ejecta shell as highly relativistic jets. We conclude that neutrino\nannihilation alone cannot power sGRBs from NS-NS mergers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Oct 2015 20:17:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 11 Jan 2016 17:06:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 12 Jan 2016 08:11:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-20"}
