embly. Using further N-body\ncalculations, it is shown that a substantial residual gas expulsion, with\n$\\approx30$% star formation efficiency, can indeed swell the newborn embedded\ncluster adequately. The limitations of the present calculations and their\nconsequences are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Oct 2015 20:19:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-21"}
