x across the full dv range. Given a predominantly old\nstellar population in these lensing galaxies, we argue that the observed large\nvelocity width and Fe-rich abundance pattern can be explained by SNe Ia\nenriched gas at radius r~r_e. We show that additional spatial constraints in\nline-of-sight velocity and relative abundance ratios afforded by a\nmulti-sightline approach provide a powerful tool to resolve the origin of\nchemically-enriched cool gas in massive halos.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Oct 2015 20:46:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 29 Feb 2016 03:17:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-23"}
